Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c (6.4%), indicating impaired glucose control or possible diabetes. All other metabolic and renal parameters are within normal limits. Lipid profile reveals low HDL cholesterol (34.9 mg/dL), which is a cardiovascular risk factor. Recommend further evaluation and management of glycemic control and measures to increase HDL.
